James A. JOHNSTON, Warden, U. S. Penitentiary, Alcatraz, Cal., v. James McNEALY. No. 9412. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 4, 1940. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., and A. J. Zirpoli, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Vincent Cullinan, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, HANEY, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein, 30 F.Supp. 312, dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
